-- Japanese Sold Net 490.5 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-03-27T23:52:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-27/japanese-sold-net-490-5-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 22 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in Tokyo.  Japanese investors sold 490.5 billion yen ($5.2 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 640.2 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 62.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 1193.2 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 975.2 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 267.6 billion yen in stocks, and sold 1214.9 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 2457.7
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
